bib_record.title: Cross-Sections For the Formation of Sb and Sc Isotopes By Irradiation of Y, La, Ta and Au with 18.2 GeV.

free_txt: Elemental Yield of Scandium For Different Targets: Cu,
Y, La, Ta, Au and U.
Two Different Li-Drifted Ge-Semiconductor
Detectors. The First of these was a 35 cm**3 Coaxially
Drifted Detector Having a Resolution of About 8-KeV at
1.33-MeV. Two Runs were Measured on a 14 cm**3 Planar
(20 CM**2) Detector with a Resolution of 4.0-4.3-KeV
At 1.33-MeV.
The Errors Obtained by the Comparison of
Gamma-Lines, Such As Statistical Counting Errors,
Errors in the Chemical Yield Measurements,
Reproducibility Found by Using Several Gamma-Lines, and
The  Errors of the Sc and Sb Monitor Cross Sections are
Included.
For the Purpose of Comparision of Yield Distributions
From Different Targets, the Errors in the Monitor Cross
Sections Which Arise from the Determination of these
Relative to the Al-27(P,N+3P)Na-24 Cross Section in
O0577.Exf and O0559.Exf Should not be Taken Into
Account.  The Errors are 7.3% and 8.5% For the Scandium
And the Antimony Yields, Respectively.
The Targets Consisted of Foils of Uranium, Gold,
Tantalum, Lanthanum and Yttrium with Thicknesses of
About 90, 45, 47, 30 and 14 mg/cm**2, Respectively.
Several Runs were Made.  The Target Foils were
Separated by Two 0.03-Mm Aluminum Foils, in Such a  Way
That Each Target Foil was Covered by Aluminum on Both
Sides So As to Catch the Recoils.  These Catcher  Foils
Were Then Chemically Treated Together with the Target
Foils to Avoid any Recoil Losses.
As the Monitor in this Experiment is the Uranium Foil.
The Cross Sections were Determined by Comparing the
Yields Nuclide by Nuclide with Those in Uranium.
